<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 832.85/54</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-01T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your November 29 [1 p.m.] in regard to French contract for German
                                ships in Brazil.</p>
                            <p>Cable as soon as you can whether it is intended to put on any
                                shipping North Atlantic trade and terms cabled in your message.
                                Arrangement apparently applies to commerce between France and Brazil
                                only.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>